tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated creatinine, proteinuria, glucosuria, and ketonuria, suggesting impaired renal function and possible glomerular involvement. Urine is cloudy, brown, and has low specific gravity. Blood glucose and HbA1c are not elevated, making diabetes unlikely. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Findings are consistent with renal dysfunction, possibly acute or chronic, and further nephrological evaluation is recommended.
